---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Pricing | Tenure"
  description="Simple pricing for Tenure. Start free with the open-source core, move to Pro for single-user production governance, choose Team for shared memory and identity, or use Enterprise for organization-wide policy and audit controls."
  canonical="https://tenureai.dev/pricing"
  keywords="Tenure pricing, AI memory pricing, AI agent governance pricing, individual AI tools, team AI memory, AI state infrastructure pricing, governed AI context, OIDC AI memory, SCIM AI memory, enterprise AI governance"
>
  <main class="pricing-page">
    <section class="pricing-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="hero-badge">
          <span class="hero-badge-dot"></span>
          Open source core · Pro governance · Team Mode · Enterprise controls
        </div>

        <h1>Start free. Add governance when Tenure becomes part of your workflow.</h1>

        <p class="hero-rag-line">
          The same deterministic context engine at every tier.
        </p>

        <p class="hero-sub">
          Use the open-source core for personal projects. Pro is for one person running production agents. Team adds shared identity and context. Enterprise adds organization-wide policy and audit controls.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="pricing-section" aria-labelledby="pricing-plans-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="label">Plans</span>
        <h2 id="pricing-plans-heading">Choose the operating model.</h2>
        <p class="pricing-intro">
          Tenure does not charge by projects, scopes, clients, or agent tokens. Pricing changes when the operating model changes: open-source development, single-user production, shared team operation, or organization-wide governance.
        </p>

        <div class="pricing-grid">
          <article class="pricing-card">
            <div class="pricing-card-topline">Open Source</div>
            <h3>Developer</h3>
            <p class="pricing-card-desc">For individuals exploring Tenure or running personal projects across their own tools.</p>

            <div class="price-row">
              <span class="price">Free</span>
            </div>
            <p class="price-note">Always free. No account or credit card required.</p>

            <a class="btn-secondary pricing-btn" href="/docs/quickstart">Get Started</a>

            <ul class="pricing-features">
              <li>Project-scoped memory</li>
              <li>Structured beliefs with provenance</li>
              <li>Scoped client and agent tokens</li>
              <li>User persona toggle</li>
              <li>Local audit logs</li>
              <li>Local/self-hosted deployment</li>
              <li>Community support</li>
            </ul>
          </article>

          <article class="pricing-card pricing-card-featured">
            <div class="pricing-pill pricing-pill-soon">Coming soon</div>
            <div class="pricing-card-topline">Individual</div>
            <h3>Pro</h3>
            <p class="pricing-card-desc">For one person relying on Tenure across production agents, tools, and projects.</p>

            <div class="price-row">
              <span class="price">$19</span>
              <span class="price-unit">/ month</span>
            </div>
            <p class="price-note">Unlimited projects, clients, and agent tokens.</p>

            <a class="btn-primary pricing-btn" href="mailto:contact@tenureai.dev?subject=Tenure%20Pro%20Early%20Access">Request Pro access</a>

            <ul class="pricing-features">
              <li>Everything in Developer</li>
              <li>Cross-project user context</li>
              <li>Advanced token and capability policies</li>
              <li>GroundEval policy enforcement</li>
              <li>Full audit history and exports</li>
              <li>Backup and restore tooling</li>
              <li>Ticket support</li>
            </ul>
          </article>

          <article class="pricing-card pricing-card-soon">
            <div class="pricing-pill pricing-pill-soon">Coming soon</div>
            <div class="pricing-card-topline">Team</div>
            <h3>Small Team</h3>
            <p class="pricing-card-desc">For multiple people using Tenure with shared identity, policy, and project context.</p>

            <div class="price-row">
              <span class="price">$25</span>
              <span class="price-unit">/ user / month</span>
            </div>
            <p class="price-note">$99/month minimum, including 4 users. $25/user/month after that.</p>

            <a class="btn-secondary pricing-btn" href="mailto:contact@tenureai.dev?subject=Tenure%20Team%20Early%20Access">Request Team access</a>

            <ul class="pricing-features">
              <li>Everything in Pro</li>
              <li>Team Mode</li>
              <li>OAuth / OIDC</li>
              <li>Per-user identity and access</li>
              <li>Project and team scopes</li>
              <li>Shared team context</li>
              <li>Centralized team audit history</li>
              <li>Ticket-only support</li>
            </ul>
          </article>

          <article class="pricing-card pricing-card-soon">
            <div class="pricing-pill pricing-pill-soon">Coming soon</div>
            <div class="pricing-card-topline">Enterprise</div>
            <h3>Organization</h3>
            <p class="pricing-card-desc">For organizations that need segmented shared memory and policy enforcement across teams.</p>

            <div class="price-row">
              <span class="price">Custom</span>
            </div>
            <p class="price-note">Annual contract. Deployment and support matched to your environment.</p>

            <a class="btn-secondary pricing-btn" href="mailto:contact@tenureai.dev?subject=Tenure%20Enterprise%20Waitlist">Join Enterprise waitlist</a>

            <ul class="pricing-features">
              <li>Everything in Team</li>
              <li>SAML SSO</li>
              <li>SCIM provisioning and deprovisioning</li>
              <li>Group-to-scope mapping</li>
              <li>Organization-wide policy controls</li>
              <li>Audit exports and retention controls</li>
              <li>Email support with faster response times</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="pricing-section pricing-boundary" aria-labelledby="pricing-boundary-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="label">The boundary</span>
        <h2 id="pricing-boundary-heading">Free to explore. Paid when you depend on it.</h2>
        <p>
          The open-source core gives every user the deterministic memory engine. Pro adds the operating layer for a single power user. Team introduces shared user identity and team context. Enterprise extends governance across the organization.
        </p>

        <div class="boundary-grid">
          <div class="boundary-card">
            <div class="boundary-label">Developer</div>
            <h3>Run the core yourself.</h3>
            <p>Use project scopes, local tokens, structured beliefs, and the core context engine without an account.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="boundary-card featured">
            <div class="boundary-label">Pro, coming soon</div>
            <h3>Govern your own agents.</h3>
            <p>Add cross-project context, advanced policies, policy enforcement, audit exports, and support without paying for team features you do not need.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="boundary-card">
            <div class="boundary-label">Team, coming soon</div>
            <h3>Operate with real users.</h3>
            <p>Add OAuth/OIDC, separate user identities, shared team memory, team scopes, and centralized administration.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="boundary-card">
            <div class="boundary-label">Enterprise, coming soon</div>
            <h3>Govern Tenure across the org.</h3>
            <p>Add SAML, SCIM, organizational scopes, policy controls, retention, exports, private deployment options, and faster support.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="pricing-section" aria-labelledby="comparison-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="label">Plan comparison</span>
        <h2 id="comparison-heading">The same core state model. Different operating guarantees.</h2>

        <div class="pricing-table-wrap">
          <table class="pricing-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Capability</th>
                <th>Developer</th>
                <th>Pro</th>
                <th>Team</th>
                <th>Enterprise</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>Project-scoped memory</td>
                <td>Included</td>
                <td>Included</td>
                <td>Included</td>
                <td>Included</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Client and agent tokens</td>
                <td>Unlimited</td>
                <td>Unlimited</td>
                <td>Unlimited</td>
                <td>Unlimited</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Cross-project user context</td>
                <td>—</td>
                <td>Included</td>
                <td>Included</td>
                <td>Policy-controlled</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>GroundEval policy enforcement</td>
                <td>—</td>
                <td>Included</td>
                <td>Included</td>
                <td>Included</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Multiple user identities</td>
                <td>—</td>
                <td>—</td>
                <td>Included</td>
                <td>Included</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Team Mode</td>
                <td>—</td>
                <td>—</td>
                <td>Included</td>
                <td>Included</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>OAuth / OIDC</td>
                <td>—</td>
                <td>—</td>
                <td>Included</td>
                <td>Included</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>SSO / SAML</td>
                <td>—</td>
                <td>—</td>
                <td>—</td>
                <td>Included</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>SCIM provisioning</td>
                <td>—</td>
                <td>—</td>
                <td>—</td>
                <td>Included</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Audit tooling</td>
                <td>Local logs</td>
                <td>Full history + export</td>
                <td>Centralized team history</td>
                <td>Advanced + retention controls</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Support</td>
                <td>Community</td>
                <td>Ticket</td>
                <td>Ticket only</td>
                <td>Email, faster response times</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="pricing-section pricing-faq" aria-labelledby="pricing-faq-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="label">FAQ</span>
        <h2 id="pricing-faq-heading">What people ask before starting.</h2>

        <div class="faq-grid">
          <div class="faq-card">
            <h3>Do we host Tenure, or do you?</h3>
            <p>You do. Tenure is self-hosted by design. Your memory, policy, audit trail, and agent activity stay inside your environment, not ours.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-card">
            <h3>Do you charge for agents, clients, or projects?</h3>
            <p>No. Tokens, clients, agents, and projects are unlimited. Individual and team pricing is based on the number of users, not the number of automated systems they run.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-card">
            <h3>Who is Pro for?</h3>
            <p>Pro is for a single developer, founder, researcher, or consultant who relies on Tenure in production and needs stronger policy, audit, policy enforcement, and support without team identity features.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-card">
            <h3>When should I move from Pro to Team?</h3>
            <p>Move to Team when more than one person needs a separate identity, shared team context, team scopes, and centralized administration. Pro remains limited to a single user operator.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-card">
            <h3>Why are Pro and Team paid if Tenure is open source?</h3>
            <p>The open-source version gives you the core deterministic state engine. Paid plans add production operating tools, advanced governance, longer-lived administration, and support while keeping the core useful on its own.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-card">
            <h3>When do we need Enterprise?</h3>
            <p>Choose Enterprise when multiple teams need segmented shared memory, centralized organizational policy, SAML or SCIM, configurable audit retention, deployment controls, and a faster support relationship.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="cta" class="pricing-cta">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="label">Get started</span>
        <h2>Govern every agent you use, even when the entire team is you.</h2>
        <p class="cta-sub">
          Start with the open-source core. Move to Pro when you depend on Tenure in production, Team when context becomes shared, and Enterprise when governance must span the organization.
        </p>

        <div class="hero-cta-row">
          <a href="mailto:contact@tenureai.dev?subject=Tenure%20Pro%20Early%20Access" class="btn-primary">Request Pro access</a>
          <a href="/docs/quickstart" class="btn-secondary">Install Free</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .pricing-page {
    --pricing-accent: var(--accent, #00a8ad);
    --pricing-accent-soft: rgba(0, 168, 173, 0.14);
    --pricing-accent-border: rgba(0, 168, 173, 0.35);
    --pricing-bg: var(--bg, #151515);
    --pricing-card: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.035);
    --pricing-card-strong: rgba(0, 168, 173, 0.075);
    --pricing-border: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    --pricing-text: var(--text, #e8e8e8);
    --pricing-muted: var(--dim, #888888);
    color: var(--pricing-text);
  }

  .pricing-page *,
  .pricing-page *::before,
  .pricing-page *::after {
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }

  .pricing-hero {
    padding: 7rem 0 4rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .pricing-hero h1 {
    max-width: 1040px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  .pricing-hero .hero-sub {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  .pricing-section {
    padding: 5rem 0;
  }

  .pricing-section h2,
  .pricing-section > .container > p {
    max-width: 940px;
  }

  .pricing-intro {
    color: var(--pricing-muted);
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .pricing-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    align-items: stretch;
  }

  .pricing-card {
    position: relative;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    min-width: 0;
    min-height: 100%;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--pricing-border);
    border-radius: 22px;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.045), var(--pricing-card));
  }

  .pricing-card-featured {
    z-index: 1;
    border-color: var(--pricing-accent-border);
    background:
      radial-gradient(circle at top, rgba(0,168,173,0.16), transparent 45%),
      linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(0,168,173,0.09), rgba(255,255,255,0.035));
    transform: translateY(-0.5rem);
  }

  .pricing-pill {
    position: absolute;
    top: -0.85rem;
    left: 1.25rem;
    padding: 0.35rem 0.65rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--pricing-accent-border);
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: #0d2728;
    color: var(--pricing-accent);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .pricing-pill-soon {
    background: #2a1f0d;
    border-color: rgba(245,158,11,0.4);
    color: #f5a623;
  }

  .pricing-card-soon {
    opacity: 0.92;
  }

  .pricing-card-topline,
  .boundary-label {
    color: var(--pricing-accent);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .pricing-card h3,
  .boundary-card h3,
  .faq-card h3 {
    margin: 0.6rem 0 0.55rem;
    color: var(--pricing-text);
  }

  .pricing-card-desc,
  .price-note,
  .boundary-card p,
  .faq-card p {
    color: var(--pricing-muted);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .pricing-card-desc {
    min-height: 6.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }

  .price-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.35rem;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0.25rem;
  }

  .price {
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 4vw, 3.35rem);
    line-height: 1;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
  }

  .price-unit {
    color: var(--pricing-muted);
    font-size: 0.92rem;
  }

  .price-note {
    min-height: 5.4rem;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 1.2rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .pricing-btn {
    box-sizing: border-box;
    width: 100%;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    text-align: center;
    margin: 0.35rem 0 1.4rem;
  }

  .pricing-features {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.7rem;
    margin: auto 0 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .pricing-features li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 1.45rem;
    color: var(--pricing-text);
    line-height: 1.45;
  }

  .pricing-features li::before {
    content: "✓";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0;
    color: var(--pricing-accent);
    font-weight: 800;
  }

  .pricing-boundary {
    background:
      linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(0,0,0,0), rgba(0,168,173,0.035), rgba(0,0,0,0));
  }

  .pricing-boundary p {
    color: var(--pricing-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .boundary-grid,
  .faq-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .boundary-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .faq-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .boundary-card,
  .faq-card {
    padding: 1.4rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--pricing-border);
    border-radius: 20px;
    background: var(--pricing-card);
  }

  .boundary-card.featured {
    border-color: var(--pricing-accent-border);
    background: var(--pricing-card-strong);
  }

  .pricing-table-wrap {
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--pricing-border);
    border-radius: 20px;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
  }

  .pricing-table {
    width: 100%;
    min-width: 980px;
    border-collapse: collapse;
  }

  .pricing-table th,
  .pricing-table td {
    padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
    text-align: left;
    vertical-align: top;
  }

  .pricing-table th {
    color: var(--pricing-accent);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    background: rgba(0,168,173,0.055);
  }

  .pricing-table td {
    color: var(--pricing-text);
  }

  .pricing-table td:first-child {
    color: var(--pricing-muted);
  }

  .pricing-table tbody tr:last-child td {
    border-bottom: 0;
  }

  .pricing-faq h2 {
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .pricing-cta {
    padding-top: 5rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 1180px) {
    .pricing-grid,
    .boundary-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }

    .pricing-card-featured {
      transform: none;
    }

    .pricing-card-desc,
    .price-note {
      min-height: unset;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .pricing-grid,
    .boundary-grid,
    .faq-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .pricing-hero {
      padding-top: 5rem;
    }

    .pricing-section {
      padding: 3.5rem 0;
    }

    .pricing-card,
    .boundary-card,
    .faq-card {
      padding: 1.2rem;
      border-radius: 18px;
    }
  }
</style>
